ZCZC OE75
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 182300 UTC
HIGH PRESSURE SITS JUST N OF FAEROES ON FRIDAY EVENING WHILE AN ATLANTIC
LOW TO THE W OF IRELAND EXTENDS A TROUGH EWARDS ACROSS THE W OF THE BRITISH
ISLES. ON SATURDAY THE HIGH PRESSURE MOVS E WHILST THE ATLANTIC TROUGH
EXTENDS FURTHER E ACROSS THE UK. OVERNIGHT INTO SUNDAY A SHALLOW LOW IS
EXP TO DEVELOP WITHIN THIS TROUGH TRACKING E ACROSS CENTRAL UK AND THE SERN
N SEA. HIGH PRESSURE DRIFTS N FM SERN FITZROY IN IT'S WAKE AND BECOMES ESTABLISHED
OVER THE UK ON MONDAY. HOWEVER A DEEP LOW PRESSURE SYSTEM IS LIKELY TO MOV
INTO THE MID-ATLANTIC BY THIS STAGE. ON FRIDAY EVENING AND SATURDAY AN AREA
OF STRG WINDS ARE EXP TO MOV N ACROSS THE N OF PORTPATRICK OCNL REACHING
NEAR GALE FORCE IN THE NE. THESE STRG WINDS ARE EXP TO EASE AWAY TO THE N
ON SUNDAY MORNING AND NO FURTHER HAZARDOUS WINDS ARE EXP DURING THE PERIOD
